feat(address): implement IPAddress (#7)
* chore(address): setup ipvx address class structure.
* feat(IPAddress Class): Implement IPAddress class
* refactor(ipvx_address): redesign IPAddress helpers
This commit: - Rewrote documentation for all constructors, accessors and overrides - Replaced raw getaddrinfo/freeaddrinfo with RAII-based AddrInfo wrapper - Simplified and clarified host/port parsing using `parse_host_port()` - Introduced `resolve_addr()` and `first_sockaddr()` for encapsulated address resolution - Updated internal address handling to prefer explicit structure reinterpretation - Removed duplicated or redundant logic and streamlined error handling
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
* fix(ipv6): improve IPv6 address parsing and validation
This commit: - Enhanced parse_host_port to strictly validate bracketed IPv6 addresses, rejecting malformed inputs such as missing ']' or trailing junk. - Improved logic to distinguish between "[v6]", "[v6]:port" and invalid formats. - Updated logic to avoid incorrect parsing of unbracketed IPv6 literals.
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
* test(ipvx): add unittests for IPAddress parsing and validation
This commit: - Added tests for IPv4 and IPv6 parsing, with and without ports. - Covered valid and invalid input formats, including malformed addresses. - Verified behavior for edge cases: whitespace, port ranges, zone IDs, unicode, etc. - Ensured coverage for copy, assignment, swap and string conversion behaviors.
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
* fix: update IPAddress class header with export modifier
This commit: - Added export modifier to IPAddress class for proper symbol visibility.
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
* test(ipvx): remove invalid assumption about colon-only input
The test `REQUIRE_THROWS_AS(IPAddress{":"}, std::invalid_argument)` has been removed because it incorrectly assumes that a colon-only address string is invalid.
On Linux (glibc), `getaddrinfo(nullptr, "")` is valid and resolves to the wildcard address with port 0 (e.g., `0.0.0.0:0`). This behavior is platform-specific and consistent with POSIX.
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
* feat(ipvx_address): validate port range and refine error messages
This commit: - Added port range validation to ensure port values are within 0-65535. - Improved error message formatting for invalid IPv6 literals. - Enhanced test cases to cover illegal host characters more precisely.
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
* test(ipaddress): enhance parsing and construction test coverage
This commit: - Added test for IPAddress construction from non-AF_INET sockaddr resets to empty - Organized host/port parsing tests into sections for whitespace, formatting, ports, invalid IPs and hostname chars - Added tests for valid IPv4-mapped IPv6 and empty host scenarios
Signed-off-by: Jint-lzxy <50296129+Jint-lzxy@users.noreply.github.com>
